Linear SVM

Fitting linear SVM on iris dataset.

svm_model <- svm(
  Species ~ ., 
  data = iris,
  kernel = "linear"
)

Plotting model in two dimensions using petal_width and petal_length.

plot(
  svm_model,
  data = iris,
  Petal.Width ~ Petal.Length,
  slice = list(Sepal.Width = 3, Sepal.Length = 4)
)

Calculate confusion matrix and missclassification rate.

pred = predict(svm_model, iris)
confusionMatrix(as.factor(iris[[5]]), as.factor(pred))$tabl
##             Reference
## Prediction   setosa versicolor virginica
##   setosa         50          0         0
##   versicolor      0         46         4
##   virginica       0          1        49
mean(ifelse(iris[[5]] == pred, 0, 1))
## [1] 0.03333333

Radial SVM

Fitting radial SVM on iris dataset.

svm_model = svm(
  Species ~ ., 
  data=iris,
  kernel = "radial"
)

Plotting model in two dimensions using width and length.

plot(
  svm_model, 
  data = iris,
  Petal.Width ~ Petal.Length,
  slice = list(Sepal.Width = 3, Sepal.Length = 4) 
)

Calculate confusion matrix and missclassification rate.

pred = predict(svm_model, iris)
confusionMatrix(as.factor(iris[[5]]), as.factor(pred))$tabl
##             Reference
## Prediction   setosa versicolor virginica
##   setosa         50          0         0
##   versicolor      0         48         2
##   virginica       0          2        48
mean(ifelse(iris[[5]] == pred, 0, 1))
## [1] 0.02666667

Tuning SVM

tmodel = tune(
  svm,
  Species~., 
  data = iris,
  ranges = list(epsilon = seq(0,1,0.1), cost = 2^(2:7))
)
best_model <- tmodel$best.model
best_model
## 
## Call:
## best.tune(METHOD = svm, train.x = Species ~ ., data = iris, ranges = list(epsilon = seq(0, 
##     1, 0.1), cost = 2^(2:7)))
## 
## 
## Parameters:
##    SVM-Type:  C-classification 
##  SVM-Kernel:  radial 
##        cost:  8 
## 
## Number of Support Vectors:  35

Plot of the best model.

plot(
  best_model, 
  data = iris,
  Petal.Width ~ Petal.Length,
  slice = list(Sepal.Width = 3, Sepal.Length = 4)  
)

Confusion matrix and missclassification rate.

pred_best_model = predict(best_model,iris)
confusionMatrix(as.factor(iris[[5]]), as.factor(pred_best_model))$tabl
##             Reference
## Prediction   setosa versicolor virginica
##   setosa         50          0         0
##   versicolor      0         48         2
##   virginica       0          0        50
mean(ifelse(iris[[5]] == pred_best_model, 0, 1))
## [1] 0.01333333
